{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id7977cebd-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1334"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1334"},"text":"§ 1334.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Preemption","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id7977cebe-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1334/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Additional statements","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Except to the extent the Secretary requires additional or different statements on any cigarette package by a regulation, by an order, by a standard, by an authorization to market a product, or by a condition of marketing a product, pursuant to the Family Smoking Prevention and Tobacco Control Act (and the amendments made by that Act), or as required under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s387c/a/2"},"text":"section 387c(a)(2) of title 21","children":[],"tail":" or "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s387t/a"},"text":"section 387t(a) of title 21","children":[],"tail":", no statement relating to smoking and health, other than the statement required by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s1333"},"text":"section 1333 of this title","children":[],"tail":", shall be required on any cigarette package."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id7977cebf-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1334/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" State regulations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"No requirement or prohibition based on smoking and health shall be imposed under State law with respect to the advertising or promotion of any cigarettes the packages of which are labeled in conformity with the provisions of this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id7977cec0-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1334/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Exception","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Notwithstanding subsection (b), a State or locality may enact statutes and promulgate regulations, based on smoking and health, that take effect after the effective date of the Family Smoking Prevention and Tobacco Control Act, imposing specific bans or restrictions on the time, place, and manner, but not content, of the advertising or promotion of any cigarettes.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id7977cec1-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/92/s5"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–92, § 5","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1965-07-27"},"text":"July 27, 1965","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/79/283"},"text":"79 Stat. 283","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/222/s2"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–222, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-04-01"},"text":"Apr. 1, 1970","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/84/88"},"text":"84 Stat. 88","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/31/dA/tII"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–31, div. A, title II","children":[],"tail":", §§ 202(a), 203, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2009-06-22"},"text":"June 22, 2009","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/123/1845"},"text":"123 Stat. 1845","children":[],"tail":", 1846.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id7977cec2-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id7977cec3-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id7977cec4-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Family Smoking Prevention and Tobacco Control Act, referred to in subsec. (a), is div. A of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/31"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–31","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2009-06-22"},"text":"June 22, 2009","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/123/1776"},"text":"123 Stat. 1776","children":[],"tail":". For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title of 2009 Amendment note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s301"},"text":"section 301 of Title 21","children":[],"tail":", Food and Drugs, and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The effective date of the Family Smoking Prevention and Tobacco Control Act, referred to in subsec. (c), probably means the date of enactment of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/31"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–31","children":[],"tail":", which was approved "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2009-06-22"},"text":"June 22, 2009","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id7977cec5-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2009—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/31/s202/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–31, § 202(a)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Except to the extent the Secretary requires additional or different statements on any cigarette package by a regulation, by an order, by a standard, by an authorization to market a product, or by a condition of marketing a product, pursuant to the Family Smoking Prevention and Tobacco Control Act (and the amendments made by that Act), or as required under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s387c/a/2"},"text":"section 387c(a)(2) of title 21","children":[],"tail":" or "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s387t/a"},"text":"section 387t(a) of title 21","children":[],"tail":", no” for “No”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/31/s203"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–31, § 203","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (c)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1970—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/222"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–222","children":[],"tail":" substituted provision that no requirement or prohibition based on smoking and health should be imposed under State law with respect to the advertising or promotion of any cigarettes which packages are labeled in conformity with the provisions of this chapter for provision that no statement relating to smoking and health should be required in the advertising of any cigarettes which packages are labeled in conformity with the provisions of this chapter."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsecs. (c), (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/222"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–222","children":[],"tail":" struck out subsecs. (c) and (d) relating to the authority of the Federal Trade Commission with respect to unfair or deceptive advertising acts or practices, and reports to Congress by the Secretary of Health, Education, and Welfare and the Federal Trade Commission. See sections 1336 and 1337 of this title."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id7977cec6-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id7977cec7-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1970 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/222/s3"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–222, § 3","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-04-01"},"text":"Apr. 1, 1970","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/84/90"},"text":"84 Stat. 90","children":[],"tail":", provided in part that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/91/222/s3"},"text":"“Section 5 of the amendment made by this Act [amending this section] shall take effect as of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1969-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1969","children":[],"tail":".”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
